            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Banira et Dolvinda e<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied> <lb n="2"/>Daedalus et Tato Icari fil<lb break="no" n="3"/><expan><abbr>i</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan> Suleis suis qui <note>sic</note> curam <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>vestra</abbr><ex>m</ex></expan> agunt iden <note>sic</note> <lb n="5"/>Cappo Icari <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Gefunden in Zweitverwendung für ein Grab. In zwei Teile gebrochen. (B): CIL 13, 05027; Walser: Z. 1: Doninda; Collart - van Berchem: Z. 1 (Ende): [et]; Collart - van Berchem; AE 1946: Z. 5 (Ende): l(ibertus).</p>
            </div>
